{
  "stem": "717.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So they asked for volunteers to go to a war camp in Poznan, which was another big city in Poland that was maybe 200 miles away.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Well, apparently there were plenty of discussions between him and my mother and my, and his sister about whether he should go or not because the, the announcement said that if they go away, if they go to that camp, they'll get food.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "They'll get living quarters.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And the families will get money, will get the payments every two weeks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he volunteered, and he went away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "May 1, 1941 was the last time I ever saw him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[SOBS] That was the day of their wedding anniversary.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They were married May 1, 1926.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] We used to get letters from him from the camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In the beginning, they even sent a photo, him and a few people that worked with him.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, and then the letters stopped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we used to get the checks for quite a while, every two weeks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't remember what it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Probably just enough to buy the food rations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this, with our logic, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we assumed that because they're still paying us, that he is alive, that he's working.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Otherwise, why would they pay?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was our logic.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] About my father, I am not sure.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know what happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One time, about two or three years later, two years-- this was '41-- maybe in '42 or '43, they sent back some people from that camp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] In fact, a neighbor of ours-- [NON-ENGLISH], I think, or [NON-ENGLISH]-- he came back from that camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
